# OPTIONAL — step 4 of the ladder in README ("How much it actually holds").
#
# Skip this for a first rollout. Local hook + CI gate + a required status check
# already cover process governance, audit, and merge-time risk review. This file
# only matters for a stronger threat model: a pull request editing the gate, its
# rules, or its workflow so that the gate passes itself.
#
# It is inert until "Require review from Code Owners" is enabled in branch
# protection for the protected branches.
#
# Replace @OWNER with the real owning user or team.

# The gate's own workflow definition — the one thing a pull request could otherwise
# rewrite to score itself green.
/.github/workflows/    @OWNER
/.github/CODEOWNERS    @OWNER

# Gate entrypoint, scoring code, and the rules it enforces.
/bin/change-assess                @OWNER
/lib/adaptive_change_governance/  @OWNER
/plugins/                         @OWNER
/.ai-governance/                  @OWNER
